    {
      "name": "Be proactive.",
      "description": "Those contemplating suicide often don\u0027t believe they can be helped, so you may have to be more proactive at offering assistance. Saying, “Call me if you need anything” is too vague. Don’t wait for the person to call you or even to return your calls. Drop by, call again, invite the person out.",
      "complete": false,
